Lección 3: Verbo TO BE interrogativo + Uso de HIS y HER explicado paso a paso

His- El-HER
/jis/

Her- Ella-She
/jer/

Ejemplo:

He is his father  --Papa de EL
      /her/              de ELLA



1) Completa el siguiente texto utilizando AM – IS – ARE / IN – ON – AT cuando sea posible

IN MY HOUSE

Hello, my name is Hector. I am in my house, in the living room with my wife, her
name is Dora. We are on the sofa. My son Miguel is with his friends in his
bedroom. My daughter Luisa is in the dining room at the table, she is with one
friend. The cat is in the basement on a sofa, and the dog is in the attic on a
box. My mother Ana is with my father Robert, they are at the garage in the car.
We live very happy together.


Practicing:


1-Is Hector with his daughter in the living room?
Esta Hector con su hija en la Sala?. 

No, Hector is with his wife in the living room. 

No, Hector esta con su esposa en la sala. 

2. Are Hector and his wife on the bed?
Esta hector y su esposa en la cama. 
No, they are in the Sofa.. 

3. Is Miguel in his bedroom with his friends?
Yes,  he is in the bedrom with friends. 

4.Is Luisa in the dining room on the table? 

NO, she is in the dining room at the table. 

5-Is the cat in the basement with the dog?.
No, el cat is in the basement and the dog is in the attic  on a box. 

6- Is Ana the daughter of Hector?
No, Ana is his mother.
No, Ana is the mother of hector. 

7-Are Ana and Robert in the garage on the car?
No, They are it the garage in the car.